  "text": "In our representation formulas are prefixed by a number that represents possible worlds in the model (similar to [CITATION_1] Chapter 8] ). Formulas are also prefixed by finite sequences of announcements corresponding to successive model restrictions. Given a finite sequence of formulas ψ k = (ψ 1 . . . ψ k ), for each 1 ≤ i ≤ k, the sequence (ψ 1 . . . ψ i ) is noted ψ i whereas ψ 0 = denotes the empty sequence. In addition, we write M |ψ k for M |ψ 1 | . . . |ψ k .",
